## Multi-tenancy
- Every Qdrant collection name equals the normalized workspace id (same as company_id in the API)
- Every BM25 index is keyed by company_id
- company_id is required on every ingestion and query request
- Never mix data across collections
- Validate company_id exists before any operation

## Infrastructure
- Qdrant, Redis, Unstructured run via docker-compose only
- Backend and ARQ worker run locally during development
- All environment variables loaded from .env via pydantic-settings
- Single .venv at project root, never per-folder venvs